    "Once well trained, DFMs can transform the input random noise to the new data.",
    "TLDifferent from the conventional ML that learns every task from scratch, TL applies the learned knowledge from the source tasks to the target task [214], as illustrated in Figure 11.",
    "TL is expected to enhance the learning performance via transferring the learned knowledge from the previous tasks, especially when the training samples in the target task are insufficient to train the model from scratch.",
    "Nevertheless, the performance of TL can be poor if the correlation between the source and target tasks is small.",
    "Comparison between model-based methods and AI-based ones for ISACAlthough various model-based methods have been well investigated for ISAC, they face several practical implementation issues, such as computational complexity and model availability, especially when the ISAC system is highly dynamic with high-dimension variables."
